BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ihLLBqz1RSuz3MEX38PMS
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260409T031156Z
DTSTART:20260412T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geometry-of-light/16795597
	/2026-04-12T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geomet
	ry-of-light/16795597/2026-04-12T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:CJ5Cw8A08QdHy1fr9WYTf
SUMMARY:Kameelah Janan Rasheed: we leak\, we exceed
DTSTAMP:20260409T031156Z
DTSTART:20260412T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Kameelah Janan Rasheed \\(b. 1985\, East Palo Alto\, CA\; lives
	 and works in Brooklyn\, NY\\) is a self-described “learner” who creates m
	ulti-media works that explore the poetics-pleasures-politics of Black know
	ledge production\, information technologies\, \\[un\\]learning\, and belie
	f formation. She often integrates found images and words alongside her own
	 writing to create collaged wall installations and experimental video work
	s. Across her work\, Rasheed investigates the revision and life cycles of 
	text\, embracing expanded and embodied forms of writing and reading.\n\nwe
	 leak\, we exceed will activate the unique volume and multiple vantage poi
	nts of the Henry’s double-height gallery\, drawing together threads from p
	hysics\, Black critical thought\, and information theory to create an imme
	rsive environment that interrogates the spatial and social implications of
	 compression. A common process used in data storage\, spatial organization
	\, and information systems\, compression abbreviates and collapses complex
	 ideas into more simplified forms. Rasheed questions the way compression c
	omes at the cost of nuance and creates unrecoverable losses. She draws par
	allels between the compression of information and the containment of peopl
	e\, both physically and through the structuring and defining of identities
	. Through a network of video\, sound\, and architectural mark-making\, Ras
	heed proposes alternatively what she calls “an embrace of Black excess and
	 expansion” as a liberatory practice.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/even
	ts/#/details/kameelah-janan-rasheed-we-leak-we-exceed/16417090/2026-04-12T
	00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/kameelah-janan-rasheed-we
	-leak-we-exceed/16417090/2026-04-12T00
LOCATION:Henry Art Gallery\, 15th Ave NE & 41st St\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vkfuTTV1lHya2FuI9-XXw
SUMMARY:You've Had It In You All Along
DTSTAMP:20260409T031156Z
DTSTART:20260412T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Artists: Barbara Earl Thomas | Tariqa Waters | Cristina Martine
	z | Robert Wade | Maikoiyo Alley-Barnes | Nahom Ghirmay “\n\nYou’ve Had It
	 In You All Along” is an affirmation of our capability to weather any stor
	m. It serves as a vital reminder that the tools required to reach your des
	tination are already etched within your spirit. We already carry the brill
	iance and the beauty of what it takes—the confidence\, the strength\, the 
	security\, the poise\, and the knowledge to achieve our goals. The grit\, 
	the rigor\, the radical ideas\, and the voice required to transcend the wo
	rld around us are not external gifts to be acquired\; they are inherent po
	wers waiting for the moment of their activation. \n\nIn the process of ove
	rcoming—when the pathway forward is unclear and the effort feels endless—i
	t is easy to lose sight of our own internal compass. When we stand face-to
	-face with rejection\, heartbreak\, or the heavy weight of difficult seaso
	ns\, this exhibition serves as a sanctuary to remind us that we have alway
	s been more than enough\, exactly as we are. Breakthroughs happen in the s
	pace where we are gentle with ourselves\, allowing for the activation of a
	n inner wisdom and intuition that has been present since our first breath.
	\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/you-ve-had-it-in-you-all
	-along/18494682/2026-04-12T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/you-ve-had-it-in-you-all-
	along/18494682/2026-04-12T00
LOCATION:Avery Barnes Gallery\, 120 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:o37UxjubIMknnT1Mcsysq
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260409T031156Z
DTSTART:20260412T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-04
	-12T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-04-12T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:C9umsIwHDGYlQ6NntYwOy
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260409T031156Z
DTSTART:20260413T070000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
